  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project will address a problem that has troubled Service members, Veterans, and
      civilians with amputations for decades, impacting satisfaction with prosthetic use, residual
      limb skin health, and negatively affecting quality of life. Prior research in this area has
      been limited and insufficient. We are confident that improving the evaluation and treatment
      of residual limb hyperhidrosis will reduce the secondary health consequences of amputation
      and will lead to improved quality of life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
